{
  "page": "Wedding of Maron Martell and Daenerys Targaryen",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Maron_Martell_%26_Daenerys_Targaryen_by_Lopata_Four.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/f/fe/Maron_Martell_%26_Daenerys_Targaryen_by_Lopata_Four.jpg/300px-Maron_Martell_%26_Daenerys_Targaryen_by_Lopata_Four.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"374\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/f/fe/Maron_Martell_%26_Daenerys_Targaryen_by_Lopata_Four.jpg/450px-Maron_Martell_%26_Daenerys_Targaryen_by_Lopata_Four.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/f/fe/Maron_Martell_%26_Daenerys_Targaryen_by_Lopata_Four.jpg/600px-Maron_Martell_%26_Daenerys_Targaryen_by_Lopata_Four.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Maron_Martell_%26_Daenerys_Targaryen_by_Lopata_Four.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>The bride and groom, Daenerys and Maron by Lopata Four</div></div></div>\n<p>The <b>wedding of Maron Martell and Daenerys Targaryen</b> occurred in <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_187_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">187&#160;AC</a> at <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a>, unifying <a href=\"/index.php/Dorne\" title=\"Dorne\">Dorne</a> with the rest of the realm under <a href=\"/index.php/House_Targaryen\" title=\"House Targaryen\">Targaryen</a> rule.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_daeron_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_daeron_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Background\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Background</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Historical_conflicts\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Historical conflicts</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Peace_through_marriage\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Peace through marriage</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Wedding\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Wedding</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Aftermath\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Aftermath</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#Attendees\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Attendees</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Background\">Background</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Wedding_of_Maron_Martell_and_Daenerys_Targaryen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Background\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Historical_conflicts\">Historical conflicts</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Wedding_of_Maron_Martell_and_Daenerys_Targaryen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Historical conflicts\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Dorne and the rest of the continent of Westeros were long at odds. For hundreds of years, Dorne defied <a href=\"/index.php/The_Reach\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"The Reach\">the Reach</a> and the <a href=\"/index.php/Stormlands\" title=\"Stormlands\">stormlands</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_daeron_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_daeron_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> The <a href=\"/index.php/Marcher_lords\" title=\"Marcher lords\">Marcher lords</a> in turn built great castles to defend against Dornish incursions.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>When <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon I Targaryen\">Aegon</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenys_Targaryen\" title=\"Rhaenys Targaryen\">Rhaenys</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Visenya_Targaryen\" title=\"Visenya Targaryen\">Visenya Targaryen</a> arrived in <a href=\"/index.php/Westeros\" title=\"Westeros\">Westeros</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon%27s_Conquest\" title=\"Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">conquered</a> the <a href=\"/index.php/Seven_Kingdoms\" title=\"Seven Kingdoms\">Seven Kingdoms</a>, establishing their <a href=\"/index.php/House_Targaryen\" title=\"House Targaryen\">House</a> as kings over all of Westeros, Dorne alone remained unconquered.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabaegon.27s_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabaegon.27s_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> They would make an attempt to conquer Dorne, but after the deaths of Queen Rhaenys and her <a href=\"/index.php/Dragon\" title=\"Dragon\">dragon</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Meraxes\" title=\"Meraxes\">Meraxes</a>, the Targaryens abandoned the ambition of conquering Dorne for a time and forged a peace with <a href=\"/index.php/Nymor_Martell\" title=\"Nymor Martell\">Nymor Martell</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/Prince_of_Dorne\" title=\"Prince of Dorne\">Prince of Dorne</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabreign_of_the_dragon_-_the_wars_of_king_aegon_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabreign_of_the_dragon_-_the_wars_of_king_aegon_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> Despite this lasting peace, other Dornish Wars and conflicts would follow from time to time, and raiders would still descend from the <a href=\"/index.php/Red_Mountains\" title=\"Red Mountains\">Red Mountains</a> to the <a href=\"/index.php/Dornish_Marches\" title=\"Dornish Marches\">Dornish Marches</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafdorne:_dorne_against_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafdorne:_dorne_against_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> Furthermore, the ancient hatred would long persist between the <a href=\"/index.php/Dornish\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Dornish\">Dornish</a> and their neighbors in the marches, <a href=\"/index.php/Stormlands\" title=\"Stormlands\">stormlands</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/The_Reach\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"The Reach\">the Reach</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_iv.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_iv.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>After the ascent of young King <a href=\"/index.php/Daeron_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Daeron I Targaryen\">Daeron I Targaryen</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_157_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">157&#160;AC</a>, the conflict between the Targaryens and Dorne reignited. Though only a boy, King Daeron quickly set his sights upon <a href=\"/index.php/Conquest_of_Dorne\" title=\"Conquest of Dorne\">completing</a> the Conquest of his ancestors and bringing Dorne into the realm. Daeron's forces reached <a href=\"/index.php/Sunspear\" title=\"Sunspear\">Sunspear</a>, where the <a href=\"/index.php/Prince_of_Dorne_(father_of_Maron)\" title=\"Prince of Dorne (father of Maron)\">Prince of Dorne</a> was forced to <a href=\"/index.php/Submission_of_Sunspear\" title=\"Submission of Sunspear\">submit</a>. Yet the <a href=\"/index.php/Smallfolk\" title=\"Smallfolk\">smallfolk</a> of Dorne proved tenacious, rising up in rebellion. Daeron himself was forced to return to put down the rebels in <a href=\"/index.php/160_AC\" title=\"160 AC\">160&#160;AC</a>. Yet, when he met with the Dornishmen under a peace banner to discuss terms, Daeron was betrayed and murdered.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_daeron_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_daeron_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Peace_through_marriage\">Peace through marriage</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Wedding_of_Maron_Martell_and_Daenerys_Targaryen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Peace through marriage\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Daeron's successor and younger brother King <a href=\"/index.php/Baelor_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Baelor I Targaryen\">Baelor I Targaryen</a> journeyed to Dorne to forge a peace. He agreed to betroth his young cousin, Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Daeron_II_Targaryen\" title=\"Daeron II Targaryen\">Daeron</a>, to the Prince of Dorne's eldest child, <a href=\"/index.php/Myriah_Martell\" title=\"Myriah Martell\">Myriah Martell</a>. The two would wed when both were of age.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_baelor_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_baelor_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup> By the time his father, King <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_IV_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon IV Targaryen\">Aegon IV Targaryen</a>, took the throne, Daeron's greatest ally was Myriah's younger brother, <a href=\"/index.php/Maron_Martell\" title=\"Maron Martell\">Maron Martell</a>, who succeeded their father as Prince of Dorne.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_iv.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_iv.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>When Daeron succeeded his father as king in <a href=\"/index.php/184_AC\" title=\"184 AC\">184&#160;AC</a>, he soon began negotiations with his good-brother, Prince Maron, to unify Dorne with the rest of the Seven Kingdoms.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_daeron_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_daeron_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> It was Daeron's hope that, where violence had failed, marriage could put an end to hostilities with Dorne.<sup id=\"cite_ref-SSM_9-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-SSM-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup> After two years of negotiation, an agreement was made to betroth Maron to Daeron's younger sister, Princess <a href=\"/index.php/Daenerys_Targaryen_(daughter_of_Aegon_IV)\" title=\"Daenerys Targaryen (daughter of Aegon IV)\">Daenerys</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_daeron_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_daeron_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> The betrothal was made despite the famed passion that Daenerys and her <a href=\"/index.php/Bastardy\" title=\"Bastardy\">bastard</a> half-brother apparently held for each other.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup> Daeron valued matters of state over matters of love,<sup id=\"cite_ref-SSM_9-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-SSM-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup> and believed the good of thousands must come before the good of just two.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup> He also did not wish to give his sister to the half-brother with whom he had sometimes clashed and many were eying as a claimant to the throne over himself.<sup id=\"cite_ref-SSM_9-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-SSM-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Wedding\">Wedding</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Wedding_of_Maron_Martell_and_Daenerys_Targaryen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Wedding\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:DaeronIIandPrinceMaronMartell_MV.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/5/54/DaeronIIandPrinceMaronMartell_MV.jpg/300px-DaeronIIandPrinceMaronMartell_MV.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"450\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/5/54/DaeronIIandPrinceMaronMartell_MV.jpg/450px-DaeronIIandPrinceMaronMartell_MV.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/5/54/DaeronIIandPrinceMaronMartell_MV.jpg/600px-DaeronIIandPrinceMaronMartell_MV.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:DaeronIIandPrinceMaronMartell_MV.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Maron and Daeron pay their respects to Baelor after the wedding by Magali Villeneuve for <i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_and_Fire\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"The World of Ice and Fire\">The World of Ice and Fire</a></i></div></div></div>\n<p>Because Daenerys was not yet of age, her wedding to Maron would not take place until a year later, in <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_187_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">187&#160;AC</a>. With the marriage, Prince Maron knelt and swore oaths of fealty to the <a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Throne\" title=\"Iron Throne\">Iron Throne</a>. He and King Daeron then departed the <a href=\"/index.php/Red_Keep\" title=\"Red Keep\">Red Keep</a> and rode to the <a href=\"/index.php/Great_Sept_of_Baelor\" title=\"Great Sept of Baelor\">Great Sept of Baelor</a>, where they laid a wreath before the feet of the statue of King Baelor and proclaimed, \"Baelor, your work is done.\" With this, the realm was unified from <a href=\"/index.php/The_Wall\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"The Wall\">the Wall</a> to the <a href=\"/index.php/Summer_Sea\" title=\"Summer Sea\">Summer Sea</a>, as Aegon the Conqueror had dreamed.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_daeron_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_daeron_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>As part of the wedding celebrations, a <a href=\"/index.php/Tourney\" title=\"Tourney\">tourney</a> was held. In the tourney, King Daeron's eldest son, Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Baelor_Targaryen_(son_of_Daeron_II)\" title=\"Baelor Targaryen (son of Daeron II)\">Baelor</a>, took a famous victory, defeating Daemon Blackfyre in the final tilt and earning the name Breakspear at the age of seventeen.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_daeron_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_daeron_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The next year, Daeron raised the castle of <a href=\"/index.php/Summerhall\" title=\"Summerhall\">Summerhall</a> in the Dornish Marches, near the boundaries of the Reach, the stormlands, and Dorne, to mark the peace forged by the wedding of Maron and Daenerys.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_daeron_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_daeron_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Aftermath\">Aftermath</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Wedding_of_Maron_Martell_and_Daenerys_Targaryen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Aftermath\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Despite the peace, not all were satisfied with the marriage. Prince Maron won a number of concessions through the union, holding greater autonomy and rights than the other great lords. Furthermore, the generations of enmity between Dorne and their neighbors was not easily set aside, and the knights and lords of the Dornish Marches came to mistrust King Daeron, looking back on days when the Dornish were not rivals for the king's attention but enemies to fight.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_daeron_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_daeron_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Displeasure with Daeron's concessions and lingering enmity with the Dornish were among the seeds of the coming <a href=\"/index.php/First_Blackfyre_Rebellion\" title=\"First Blackfyre Rebellion\">Blackfyre Rebellion</a>. Many lords unhappy with King Daeron began to turn to his bastard half-brother, Daemon Blackfyre.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_daeron_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_daeron_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Supposedly, Daeron's choice to give Daenerys to Maron over him helped lead Daemon to rebellion.<sup id=\"cite_ref-SSM_9-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-SSM-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup> Although both he and Daenerys had a number of children with their respective spouses, and Daenerys was a loyal wife to Maron,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_daeron_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_daeron_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Daemon's supporters claimed it was for love of Daenerys that he rebelled.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>For <a href=\"/index.php/House_Martell\" title=\"House Martell\">House Martell</a>, the union between Maron and Daenerys would be an important influence in the generations that followed. Maron built the <a href=\"/index.php/Water_Gardens\" title=\"Water Gardens\">Water Gardens</a> for his bride, which became a gathering place for the children of both House Martell and those of their lords and smallfolk. The wisdom taught by Daenerys to her and Maron's <a href=\"/index.php/Maron_Martell%27s_son\" title=\"Maron Martell&#39;s son\">heir</a> would be passed through the generations of Princes and Princesses of Dorne all the way to Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Doran_Martell\" title=\"Doran Martell\">Doran Martell</a>, the present Prince of Dorne.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Attendees\">Attendees</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Wedding_of_Maron_Martell_and_Daenerys_Targaryen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Attendees\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Targaryen\" title=\"House Targaryen\"><img alt=\"House Targaryen.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/20px-House_Targaryen.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/30px-House_Targaryen.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/40px-House_Targaryen.svg.png 2x\" /></a> King <a href=\"/index.php/Daeron_II_Targaryen\" title=\"Daeron II Targaryen\">Daeron II Targaryen</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Targaryen\" title=\"House Targaryen\"><img alt=\"House Targaryen.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/20px-House_Targaryen.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/30px-House_Targaryen.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/40px-House_Targaryen.svg.png 2x\" /></a> Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Baelor_Targaryen_(son_of_Daeron_II)\" title=\"Baelor Targaryen (son of Daeron II)\">Baelor Targaryen</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Blackfyre\" title=\"House Blackfyre\"><img alt=\"House Blackfyre 2.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/a/a3/House_Blackfyre_2.svg/20px-House_Blackfyre_2.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/a/a3/House_Blackfyre_2.svg/30px-House_Blackfyre_2.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/a/a3/House_Blackfyre_2.svg/40px-House_Blackfyre_2.svg.png 2x\" /></a> Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Daemon_I_Blackfyre\" title=\"Daemon I Blackfyre\">Daemon Blackfyre</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Wedding_of_Maron_Martell_and_Daenerys_Targaryen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap mw-references-columns\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_daeron_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_daeron_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_daeron_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_daeron_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\">1.2</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_daeron_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\">1.3</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_daeron_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-4\">1.4</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_daeron_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-5\">1.5</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_daeron_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-6\">1.6</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_daeron_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-7\">1.7</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_daeron_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-8\">1.8</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, The Targaryen Kings: Daeron II.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_daeron_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_daeron_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">2.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_daeron_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\">2.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, The Targaryen Kings: Daeron I.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, The Stormlands.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rfabaegon.27s_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabaegon.27s_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i>, Aegon's Conquest.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rfabreign_of_the_dragon_-_the_wars_of_king_aegon_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabreign_of_the_dragon_-_the_wars_of_king_aegon_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i>, Reign of the Dragon - The Wars of King Aegon I.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiafdorne:_dorne_against_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafdorne:_dorne_against_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, Dorne: Dorne Against the Dragons.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_iv.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_iv.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\">7.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_iv.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-1\">7.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, The Targaryen Kings: Aegon IV.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_baelor_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_baelor_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, The Targaryen Kings: Baelor I.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-SSM-9\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-SSM_9-0\">9.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-SSM_9-1\">9.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-SSM_9-2\">9.2</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-SSM_9-3\">9.3</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"/index.php/So_Spake_Martin\" title=\"So Spake Martin\">So Spake Martin</a>: <a class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.westeros.org/Citadel/SSM/Entry/6539\">Asshai.com Interview in Barcelona (July 28, 2012)</a>.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Radwd3